1
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:57,440
What does the question mean?

2
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:58,960
Read it out loud.

3
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:00,400
On the park lawn,

4
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:02,000
people wander and linger,

5
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,560
and throw fruit peels and paper scraps.

6
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:05,489
Please design a slogan for the lawn

7
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:07,680
to urge pedestrians to protect it.

8
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:09,920
Look at what you wrote.

9
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:11,480
Read it out loud.

10
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:13,880
Today you step on its head,

11
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:16,360
tomorrow it grows on your grave.

12
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:19,160
What is all this mess?

13
00:01:20,520 --> 00:01:22,380
Did you copy it from the internet?

14
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:25,340
Enough.

15
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:27,680
Rewrite it ten times.

16
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:36,000
Sister, you're finally back.

17
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,920
Let me tell you,

18
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:40,650
looking for your sister won't help, understand?

19
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,000
Sister, what is this?

20
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,259
Did you bring it for me?

21
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:44,560
Xiaocen,

22
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:46,920
why did you bring a balloon back?

23
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,560
Is it for me?

24
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,920
I don't want it. So childish.

25
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,180
How could it be for you?

26
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,400
Aunt, look at my sister.

27
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,720
She just smiles and ignores your questions,

28
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,040
and wastes her time on toys.

29
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,760
You should go teach her a lesson.

30
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,840
You're full of excuses now, aren't you?

31
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,640
Sit back down.

32
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,280
Xu Xiao,

33
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,440
thank you for the balloon.

34
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,370
You're welcome.

35
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,970
I'm glad you like it.

36
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,120
The ceramic stapling technique can repair porcelain.

37
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,360
For your artwork,

38
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,680
ceramic stapling can help you put the sherds

39
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,120
together more securely.

40
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:53,610
But kintsugi is different.

41
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,880
Kintsugi can repair not only porcelain

42
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:58,200
but also wood, ivory, bamboo, jade,

43
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,800
purple clay, and other materials.

44
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,520
In this way,

45
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:01,680
you can use

46
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:03,400
more materials in your artwork.

47
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,360
There is more space

48
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,020
to unleash your imagination.

49
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,560
You are bleeding.

50
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:11,810
I'm fine.

51
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,040
Where is the first-aid kit?

52
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:14,700
Over there.

53
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:17,680
Xia Qing.

54
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,400
Let me see.

55
00:03:21,079 --> 00:03:21,560
Look.

56
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:24,370
Does it hurt?

57
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:25,420
Be careful.

58
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,170
I'm fine.

59
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,320
It's okay.

60
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,600
I'm used to it

61
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:30,020
over the years.

62
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,440
I can handle it myself.

63
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,040
Thank you.

64
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:12,810
You're back.

65
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,160
Mom, Aunt.

66
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,040
Xiaocen.

67
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:16,880
Are you tired?

68
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,040
I'm fine.

69
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,000
Let me tell you,

70
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,800
you shouldn't go to that studio.

71
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,480
I really shouldn't.

72
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:28,320
Look,

73
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,940
she went right back in as soon as she got home.

74
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:55,360
What kept you busy today?

75
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,920
What am I trying to say?

76
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:08,760
What am I so sad about?

77
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:19,850
Xiaocen.

78
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:21,850
Morning.

79
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:23,410
Morning.

80
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,180
Why did you get here

81
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,780
so early today?

82
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,920
Did everything go well this weekend

83
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,800
with Xia Qing?

84
00:05:35,159 --> 00:05:36,290
It went pretty well.

85
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,900
Xia Qing has made great progress.

86
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,360
Whether it's ceramic stapling or kintsugi,

87
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,620
she has mastered some basic techniques.

88
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,050
We are preparing to make

89
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,880
a piece with more complex craftsmanship.

90
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:52,340
We plan to combine broken porcelain pieces, bamboo, and wood.

91
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,890
You'll see when you come to the studio.

92
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:56,720
By the way.

93
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:00,920
Why didn't you come to the studio this weekend?

94
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,600
I was wondering

95
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:08,920
if Xia Qing doesn't need me anymore.

96
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,600
Why would you think that?

97
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,480
Didn't you see it too?

98
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,920
I can't be of any help if I go.

99
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,720
Xia Qing was afraid I'd feel awkward,

100
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,650
so she found something for me to do.

101
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:26,280
What's the point?

102
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,980
Don't you think you should

103
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,240
discuss this with everyone?

104
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,080
You can just tell Xia Qing.

105
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,130
Since you guys are so close anyway.

106
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,730
That's so impolite.

107
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:44,520
Xiaocen.

108
00:06:46,159 --> 00:06:49,080
I remember you're not the kind of person to give up halfway.

109
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:49,920
What's wrong with you?

110
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,580
I just don't want to go anyway.

111
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:01,400
Every day, only Xu Xiao arrives earlier than me.

112
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:02,200
It seems our class

113
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,080
is getting another good student.

114
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,490
I just finished streaming.

115
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,050
Come have some watermelon.

116
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:15,240
Xu Xiao is back. Come have some watermelon.

117
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,880
You guys go ahead and eat.

118
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,080
Where is Xiaocen?

119
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:20,480
Didn't she say she'd come over after class?

120
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,560
She's not coming.

121
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,160
Something came up again?

122
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,780
She's never coming again.

123
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,440
I'll go inside first.

124
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,820
What's wrong with him?

125
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:35,409
What's going on?

126
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:27,800
Class,

127
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:31,280
At this stage, we have learned kintsugi restoration.

128
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,159
Regarding kintsugi restoration,

129
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,159
since ancient times,

130
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,840
there has been controversy.

131
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,400
Should kintsugi restoration

132
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:40,860
maintain the original beauty of the object,

133
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:43,120
or should it undergo a

134
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,160
What about secondary creation?

135
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,240
Respecting the original beauty of the object

136
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,600
and giving it a new appearance

137
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,120
are actually not contradictory.

138
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,920
I think a good restorer

139
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,460
can find a certain balance between them.

140
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,560
Very good.

141
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:00,340
When we restore cultural relics,

142
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,160
sometimes

143
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,800
we have to converse with history.

144
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,000
But sometimes,

145
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,520
we may have to connect with the future.

146
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:11,480
If

147
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,040
we treat an object

148
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,640
as a person,

149
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,480
a person needs to persevere.

150
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:19,120
But don't we also need to learn,

151
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,680
constantly develop, and change

152
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,120
to improve ourselves?

153
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,740
Regarding this question,

154
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:28,680
I hope everyone can come up with their own answers.

155
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,200
Are you going back to the classroom?

156
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,530
Where are you going?

157
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,690
I'm handing in my assignment to Mr. Liang.

158
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,520
How is your project with Sister Xia Qing coming along?

159
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:00,080
The artwork for the exhibition is basically done.

160
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,520
See, I told you.

161
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,800
It won't make a difference if I'm not there.

162
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:12,680
Actually,

163
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:13,800
how did you do on the exam, Zhu Pan?

164
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:14,640
I did okay.

165
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:15,400
I did pretty well.

166
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,800
These are all from the scope the professor gave us.

167
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,800
When was it given?

168
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:18,480
Why don't I remember?

169
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,480
Wasn't it sent to the group chat?

170
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,840
You just didn't check the messages.

171
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,520
If you saw it, why didn't you tell me?

172
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:24,250
That's your own problem, okay?

173
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,620
Actually, I didn't help much either.

174
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,200
Xiaqing

175
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,900
has always been an excellent person.

176
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:32,840
Unlike me,

177
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:34,640
I'm slow at learning everything.

178
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:35,280
No.

179
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:37,520
Xiaocen.

180
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:39,920
To me,

181
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,810
you've always been a very important partner.

182
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:49,000
Right. It's always like this.

183
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,560
Excuse me.

184
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,890
Why do they always make us move things?

185
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,860
Can't they find someone else?

186
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,000
Exactly.

187
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,000
Excuse me.

188
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,240
Slow down.

189
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,520
They asked you last time,

190
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,480
and now they asked me.

191
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:03,680
Yes, exactly.

192
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,320
Then I'll get going.

193
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,320
Xu Xiao.

194
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,580
About the exhibition,

195
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,880
I thought of some people who could help you.

196
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,520
Careful coming down.

197
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:01,280
Watch out.

198
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:02,240
Xiaqing.

199
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:03,320
Put it here?

200
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,660
Put it on the shelf.

201
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:05,280
Slow down.

202
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:05,880
Okay.

203
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,280
There are cold and hot ones.

204
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:18,960
Careful.

205
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:19,560
Hold it.

206
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,220
Pass it over. Pass it that way.

207
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,080
I'll have the matcha one.

208
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,040
Here, this is for you.

209
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:23,500
Thanks.

210
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:24,280
Are there any others?

211
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,410
Have a cup, Xiaqing.

212
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:26,400
Any more straws?

213
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:26,800
Straws.

214
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,200
You drink it.

215
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:27,720
Give me another cup.

216
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:28,040
Here are some more.

217
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:28,320
Thanks.

218
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,480
Who doesn't have a straw yet?

219
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,940
Since everyone is here, I'll say a few words.

220
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,480
Thank you all very much for coming today

221
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,120
and helping us out.

222
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,200
On behalf of the studio,

223
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,800
I sincerely thank everyone.

224
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,560
You're too polite, Jingjing.

225
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,280
It's the least we could do.

226
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,000
I believe this exhibition will be a huge success.

227
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,120
We'll all come and see it.

228
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,450
Let me tell you a secret.

229
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,900
I've invested my entire net worth

230
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:48,980
into this exhibition.

231
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,240
So please, everyone,

232
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:52,200
on WeChat and Weibo,

233
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,200
help me promote it.

234
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,560
If you help me promote it,

235
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:59,370
I'll cover your milk tea for a week.

236
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,320
That's great.

237
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,240
Thank you, Jing.

238
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,240
Jing is so generous.

239
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,000
Jing is so generous.

240
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,660
We should start promoting it.

241
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:16,120
Then...

242
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:16,680
Well...

243
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:23,410
Get some rest early.

244
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:27,180
Good night.

245
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:29,020
Good night.

246
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,720
I should apologize to him

247
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,680
for the studio issue.

248
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,000
Of course he likes you.

249
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:47,720
He doesn't get off at that stop,

250
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,760
but he insists on walking you home every time.

251
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:52,020
If that's not liking you, then what is it?

252
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,000
It's possible

253
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,560
that he's just a really nice guy

254
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:57,600
and is worried about my safety going back alone.

255
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:58,320
Come on.

256
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,440
If he's really that nice,

257
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,700
why doesn't he walk the whole class home?

258
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,340
Then Yuexin, what should I do?

259
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,680
Xiaocen.

260
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,320
Have you ever thought

261
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:18,760
that you

262
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,880
don't necessarily have to wait for him to make the first move?

263
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:22,920
I think we girls

264
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:26,120
can also take the initiative to pursue the people we like.

265
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,160
What's wrong?

266
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,640
I still can't believe he likes me.

267
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,320
Why?

268
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,280
You're so pretty, smart,

269
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,480
and hardworking.

270
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,660
If I were Xu Xiao, I would like you too.

271
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:40,920
Thank you, Yuexin.

272
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:41,800
Be confident.

273
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:03,880
Yuexin.

274
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:05,600
You're finally here.

275
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:08,800
This is really well made.

276
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,660
This one. This one looks the best.

277
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:39,400
We'll get going then.

278
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,000
Bye.

279
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,040
Bye.

280
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:41,760
Thanks. Bye.

281
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:42,360
Take care.

282
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,640
It's already afternoon.

283
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:48,580
Why are only regulars showing up?

284
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:53,720
Walk-ins aren't important.

285
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,320
The important one is Mr. Qin.

286
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:57,450
As long as Mr. Qin likes Xiaqing's work

287
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,640
and invests in our brand,

288
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,930
this exhibition will be a success.

289
00:17:05,839 --> 00:17:06,839
This glaze color is really beautiful.

290
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:07,160
Yes.

291
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:09,170
Please don't mind the small scale.

292
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:11,760
Tianyuan.

293
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:13,599
Come.

294
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:18,440
Let me introduce you.

295
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:19,880
These are the partners

296
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,079
of our Banlan Studio.

297
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:22,480
Let me specially introduce

298
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,480
this one.

299
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:25,079
This is our ceramic artist,

300
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:25,880
Fang Xiaqing.

301
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:26,960
Nice to meet you.

302
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:27,819
Hello, Mr. Qin.

303
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:31,120
Next, we'll let Xiaqing

304
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,080
show you around.

305
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:33,280
She can introduce things to you.

306
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:33,720
Okay.

307
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,620
Come, please this way.

308
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:38,040
This is

309
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:40,040
our main exhibition area this time.

310
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:41,520
We also have

311
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:43,320
many excellent works this time.

312
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,960
The name of this work is "Glory",

313
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:47,220
because it shines like butterfly wings.

314
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:48,050
And this work

315
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,480
is called "Bad Company".

316
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,800
One of the porcelain pieces has the word Ziqi engraved on it.

317
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:52,960
Perhaps this name...

318
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,890
Mr. Qin keeps nodding and smiling.

319
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,460
This looks promising.

320
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:57,840
Really?

321
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:00,780
He seems to be just responding politely.

322
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,580
I've looked at all your works.

323
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:07,970
They're quite good.

324
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,560
I'll keep following your work.

325
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:12,760
Please, don't see me out.

326
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,290
Goodbye.

327
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,600
I'll walk you out.

328
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:15,280
Take care.

329
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:38,970
What did Mr. Qin say?

330
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:43,330
Pretty good.

331
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:44,720
He said

332
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,480
he really appreciates Xiaqing's works.

333
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,520
He also thinks Xiaqing has the potential

334
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:50,650
to become an artist.

335
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,600
But

336
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:59,360
he thinks Xiaqing's works are too intricate

337
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:00,680
and too unique.

338
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:03,280
So, as commercial products,

339
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,610
they are hard to mass-produce.

340
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,330
Let's drink a toast.

341
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:26,280
Cheers.

342
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,640
I have something to tell you all.

343
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:50,160
We might

344
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:53,370
have to move out next month.

345
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:55,760
Move out?

346
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,160
The studio's equipment,

347
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:59,200
rent, utilities,

348
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:00,520
daily expenses,

349
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:02,480
including this exhibition.

350
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,000
I've emptied my savings.

351
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:08,320
I thought Mr. Qin could invest

352
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:12,160
so we could pay next month's rent.

353
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,360
Can't we live together anymore?

354
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,690
I was thinking we rent a small place first,

355
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:21,920
and then when we get through this period

356
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,600
and have some money on hand...

357
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:28,440
Actually,

358
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:30,140
I'm also wondering

359
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:32,020
if I should move out of Jingdezhen

360
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:34,330
and go back to a regular job.

361
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:35,690
Why are you leaving too?

362
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,890
I'm just thinking about it.

363
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:41,760
It's my fault.

364
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:44,120
I'm sorry.

365
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,700
I disappointed everyone.

366
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:46,800
Don't think like that.

367
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:47,960
Yeah, Xiaqing.

368
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,200
It's not your fault.

369
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:52,240
If anyone is to blame, it's that Mr. Qin.

370
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:53,120
Stop it.

371
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:57,560
It's my problem.

372
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,400
I was too naive.

373
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:04,690
I wanted to win too much.

374
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:07,360
I didn't understand the business model at all.

375
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,760
I lost, and I admit it.

376
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:14,060
What just makes me feel a bit bad is

377
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,880
that I made you work for nothing for so long.

378
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,010
I feel really sorry.

379
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:20,120
Don't say that.

380
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:21,560
Not at all.

381
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:33,440
We didn't lose.

382
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:37,880
At least Xia Qing's works

383
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:38,960
truly moved me.

384
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:41,400
Especially the one

385
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,330
called 'freshman'.

386
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,360
Although I don't know

387
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,330
why that piece has no story introduction,

388
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,880
I saw a kind of power in it.

389
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,440
A power that I need

390
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:56,560
but lack.

391
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,120
Sorry, I...

392
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:03,280
I'm not good at speaking.

393
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,900
What I want to tell everyone is

394
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:07,880
that we really did

395
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:09,480
something very meaningful.

396
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:17,960
Xiaocen is right.

397
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:23,160
This piece

398
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,760
is something I want to give to all of you.

399
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:28,960
If

400
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:31,000
I hadn't come to Jingdezhen,

401
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,460
hadn't met you all,

402
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:34,760
and if you hadn't recognized me,

403
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:36,770
accepted me,

404
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:38,360
supported me,

405
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,200
and protected me,

406
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:45,720
I wouldn't have had the courage to face my past.

407
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,040
Moreover,

408
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:51,040
I could never have finished this piece.

409
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,000
So,

410
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:54,520
this new life is a gift from all of you.

411
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:11,370
With your words,

412
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,880
I have the courage to start over.

413
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:15,800
If it doesn't work this time,

414
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:16,880
we'll try again next time.

415
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:18,640
It will work out eventually, right?

416
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:19,680
Yes, absolutely.

417
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,460
Tomorrow we'll

418
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:23,520
set up a stall in Taoxichuan.

419
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:25,280
The worst case is just starting over.

420
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:26,760
What's there to be afraid of?

421
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:27,160
Right.

422
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,600
Then I won't leave either.

423
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:30,660
I'll stay with you.

424
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,200
Great, together.

425
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,000
Cheers.

426
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:35,840
We won't go home until we're drunk tonight.

427
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:36,440
Cheers.

428
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:54,490
Xiaocen.

429
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:57,000
Xia Qing.

430
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,120
Thank you, Xia Qing.

431
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:22,330
Xiaocen,

432
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,060
what are you doing here all alone?

433
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:27,680
I'm just spacing out.

434
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:32,160
Xiaocen.

435
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:33,920
Here.

436
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:42,800
You know what?

437
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,440
Actually,

438
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:48,410
I've always felt that you and I are very alike.

439
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:57,320
You are so excellent,

440
00:24:59,160 --> 00:24:59,800
while I...

441
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:01,280
See,

442
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:04,130
this is the problem with both of us.

443
00:25:06,360 --> 00:25:08,490
We always think we're not good enough.

444
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:13,440
So even someone as excellent as you

445
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:16,520
can feel like she's not good enough.

446
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:19,560
Xiaocen,

447
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:21,760
you know what?

448
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:23,800
The creation of 'Freshman'

449
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:26,460
wouldn't have happened without Xu Xiao's help,

450
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:29,850
but more importantly, without the inspiration you gave me.

451
00:25:29,880 --> 00:25:30,720
Me?

452
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:32,360
Haven't you noticed?

453
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,400
Beneath those flowers,

454
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,960
the human face made of ruins

455
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:39,050
came from the doodles in your sketchbook.

456
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,320
Xiaocen.

457
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:48,290
If you really like someone,

458
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,090
you have to be brave.

459
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:51,090
Don't be afraid,

460
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:52,890
and don't back down.

461
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:54,930
You must believe

462
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:57,010
that you are worthy of love.

463
00:25:58,360 --> 00:25:59,620
Worthy of everything.

464
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:10,840
But...

465
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:15,480
he and you...

466
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:18,400
What?

467
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:21,480
He and you aren't...

468
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:34,140
Xiaocen, you misunderstood.

469
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:36,440
That day, Xu Xiao was just bandaging me up.

470
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:38,240
You're the only one who can't see it.

471
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:40,320
Everyone in our studio can tell

472
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:42,050
that he really cares about you.

473
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:01,770
Thank you for coming to help today,

474
00:27:01,840 --> 00:27:03,370
and giving me so many ideas.

475
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:05,120
It's fine. Hurry back to school

476
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:06,040
before it gets late.

477
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:06,400
Okay.

478
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,120
We'll be leaving then.

479
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:08,240
Goodbye, Sister Xiaqing.

480
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:09,120
Bye. Take care.

481
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:10,080
Alright. Bye.

482
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:11,000
Watch out for cars.

483
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:11,600
Take care.

484
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:36,840
You're the only one who can't tell.

485
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,960
Everyone in our studio can see it.

486
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,420
He really cares about you.

487
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:00,180
Can I listen...

488
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:04,240
What's wrong?

489
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:06,700
Can I listen to the song you're listening to?

490
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:42,120
Right now, he is by my side.

491
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:45,380
We are listening to the same song.

492
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,360
I guess this is a step forward.

493
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:54,610
It's good enough like this for now.

494
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:57,520
Taking it slow is fine.

495
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:02,560
There is still a long time left in college.

496
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:06,600
There will definitely be a right time in the future

497
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:09,480
when I can express to Xu Xiao

498
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:11,200
my true feelings.

499
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,370
This is good enough for now.

500
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:19,000
This is good enough.

501
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:26,080
I like you.
